    <div class="kicker">
      <time class="updated" datetime="2009-07-29T08:01:00+00:00">Wednesday, July 29, 2009</time>
    </div>
    <h1 class="title" >
      <a href="index.html?p=958">Some idea</a>
    </h1>
  </header>
  <div class="post-content" itemprop="articleBody">
    <p>So, <a href="http://orangette.blogspot.com/2009/07/its-all-there.html">Delancey</a> is opening its doors on Wednesday, August 12, at 5:00 pm. I‚Äôm a little short on words to describe how I feel about that, but maybe this picture will give you some idea.</p>
<p><a href="wp-content/uploads/2015/09/bea3c-meshockedinpb1.jpg"><img decoding="async" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5363402338421265394" class="aligncenter" src="wp-content/uploads/2015/09/bea3c-meshockedinpb1.jpg?w=231" alt="" border="0" /></a></p>
<p>Brandon feels pretty much the same, I think. Maybe with a touch of queasy on top. Or maybe I‚Äôm just projecting. Hard to say.</p>
<p><a href="wp-content/uploads/2015/09/b7bc0-bdpinbooth1.jpg"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5363403280127178034" class="aligncenter" src="wp-content/uploads/2015/09/b7bc0-bdpinbooth1.jpg?w=227" alt="" width="310" height="410" border="0" /></a></p>
<p>Nah, actually, we‚Äôre very, <span style="font-style: italic;">very </span>excited. This is the part that we‚Äôve been waiting for. It‚Äôs been a long time coming, and though I don‚Äôt know that we‚Äôll ever feel completely ready, we‚Äôre close. Or close enough. I just hope we get some sleep sometime soon, because apparently, I‚Äôm already having a hard time keeping my eyes open.</p>
<p><a href="wp-content/uploads/2015/09/e2a93-meincredulousinpb1.jpg"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5363404739878399362" class="aligncenter" src="wp-content/uploads/2015/09/e2a93-meincredulousinpb1.jpg?w=231" alt="" width="467" height="607" border="0" /></a></p>
<p>And we‚Äôre in the middle of a record-breaking heat wave. The restaurant has no air conditioning. I‚Äôm going to sit here and massage my temples for a while. That‚Äôll help.</p>
<p><a href="wp-content/uploads/2015/09/3ee55-meheadacheinpb1.jpg"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5363755708896354802" class="aligncenter" src="wp-content/uploads/2015/09/3ee55-meheadacheinpb1.jpg?w=230" alt="" width="467" height="610" border="0" /></a></p>
<p>But hey, you know, today is the fifth anniversary of this blog. <span style="font-style: italic;">Five</span> years. Five years! It‚Äôs pretty amazing. <span style="font-style: italic;">You‚Äôre</span> pretty amazing, people! Thank you. You make me so happy.</p>
<p><a href="wp-content/uploads/2015/09/a8cd4-meandbdpsillypb1.jpg"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5363760291779352642" class="aligncenter" src="wp-content/uploads/2015/09/a8cd4-meandbdpsillypb1.jpg?w=234" alt="" width="468" height="600" border="0" /></a></p>
<p>And it‚Äôs also our second wedding anniversary. That‚Äôs not so bad either.</p>
<p>Between now and the 12th, we‚Äôre holding soft opening dinners. My mother arrives today to lend a hand, and then my in-laws come next week. I might not be able to write a coherent sentence for a while, but I‚Äôll have photographs for you. For sure. See you in a couple of days.</p>
<p>P.S. To those who have asked questions about various aspects (lights, desserts, etc.) of the restaurant: I promise, <span style="font-style: italic;">promise</span>, to answer them soon. I could talk about that stuff all day.</p>
<p>P.P.S. For local readers: I‚Äôm so, so sorry to say that the soft opening dinners are sold out. We opened them first to family and friends, and then to a mailing list that Brandon has been compiling, and they went <span style="font-style: italic;">fast</span>. We can hardly believe it. But if you would like to get information about future special events at Delancey, please send an e-mail to delanceyseattle (at) gmail (dot) com with ‚Äúmailing list‚Äù written in the subject line.</p>
  </div>
