    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Molly,</p>
<p>Never commented on your blog before, but congrats!</p>
<p>I&#39;m a relatively new reader, as I just randomly picked up your book at the local B&#038;N and began reading a few months ago.</p>
<p>One word&#8230;breathtaking.</p>
<p>You summed up all I have felt about food in my life.  It left me laughing randomly in an airport, crying while reading late at night in bed, and often just smiling to myself at random points during my day only to have my husband ask &#8220;you ok?&#8221;  I had to read slowly so I could savor each page.  </p>
<p>The book has earned it&#39;s spot on my kitchen counter with my other books, and it&#39;s a spot I hold dear.</p>
<p>Thank you.  Thank you for being real and connected to what you do.  It&#39;s a true inspiration in life üôÇ</p>
<p>And congrats on your anniversary and restaurant.  My husband and I took our honeymoon in Seattle; it&#39;s truly an intoxicating place.  Hope we can visit your niche there soon!</p>
<p>-Alisha</p>
